
Answer file: ans12.sh

Program expects 1 or 2 command line arguments (CLAs).
  if 1 CLA,  print file $1 as one long line.
  if 2 CLAs, print file $1 with $2 words per line.

e.g.:
> ./ans12.sh que12.in 6
This is a file that has
a number of words and lines
in it.
> ./ans12.sh que12.in
This is a file that has a number of words and lines in it.
> 

Hint: xargs -n 
